{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d889b1e2-b397-4215-ac1a-97b73807fc0b","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then:**\n```bash\ndotnet --version          # verify SDK 11.0.100+ is installed\ndotnet restore            # pull updated packages\ndotnet build              # confirm it compiles\ndotnet test               # run tests\n```\n\nAlso update any NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.*`) to their 11.x versions. Check the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) for anything that affects your app.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2f79528f-2d82-4751-a347-4fcea057677a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to search their codebase since they've described the files involved.","outputTokens":348,"requestId":"6820:222B59:5FA0857:68824C8:69F010DE"},"id":"f870f3a0-116b-4451-9123-4f42e3f13dc1","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:44:06.187Z","parentId":"3f928780-6ab2-4a04-a051-1ed26c58c7a6"}
